    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope for 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw",
      "description": "Screw outer diameter: 7.0–8.0 mm. Rod diameter: 5.5–6.0 mm. Construct offset (screw tip to rod centerline): 35–45 mm per ASTM F1717 fixture geometry. Applied axial compressive load: 0–2400 N. Applied bending moment: 0–18 Nm. Crosshead displacement rate: 5 mm/min (quasi-static). Test temperature: 20–25 degrees C ambient. UHMWPE block density: 0.94–0.96 g/cm3. All boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 Section 8 fixture constraints. Model applicability is bounded to these ranges; extrapolation outside these bounds is not supported by this COU."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw applicability constraint",
      "description": "This COU applies exclusively to non-cannulated pedicle screws with nominal outer diameter 7.5 mm (tolerance +/-0.5 mm), manufactured from Ti-6Al-4V ELI per ASTM F136, used in conjunction with 5.5–6.0 mm diameter titanium alloy rods and standard polyaxial heads. Cannulated variants, screws outside the 7.0–8.0 mm diameter band, alternative alloys (CoCr, stainless steel), and dynamic or fatigue loading conditions are explicitly excluded. Validation data (N=11 constructs, two independent laboratories) were collected within these bounds and include both boundary-proximate specimens (7.0 mm and 8.0 mm diameter lots)."
    }
  },
